The XRD spectra of samples (i-iii) are given in Fig. 1
                        a. Fig. 1a depicts that all diffraction peaks are consistent with the standard card of PDF#75–0694 (K2SiF6) (Table 2
                        ). There are no other obvious impurity peaks, indicating that the GQDs and K2SiF6 coating do not change the physical phase of the KSF:0.05Mn4+ phosphor [15].

For exploring the mechanism of NTQE, the integrated emission intensity curves of the Stokes peaks (I

                           s
                        ) and the anti-Stokes peaks (I

                           as
                        ) of the samples (i-iii) at 30–270 °C are given in Fig. 7e. From Fig. 7e, it can be observed that before 210 °C, the curves of the anti-Stokes peak (I

                           as
                        ) and the curves of the Stokes peak (I

                           s
                        ) show an upward trend with the increase of temperature, and the rising trend of the I

                           as
                         curve is greater than that of the I

                           s
                         curve.
